cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with visual odometry, which is a subfield of computer vision and robotics. The use of multi-spectral sensors and the focus on image alignment suggest that this paper is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. However, the use of bundle adjustment and the focus on robotics suggest that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of machine learning techniques for feature matching could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the use of 3D reconstruction techniques could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) category.
